race.description: Congrats Steph Laycock Qtis 3YO Maiden Hcp
race.comment: FAR CRY (3) improved sharply second-up, beaten a whisker over 1680m at Ipswich, letting down nicely from the pace. Jumps from the inside gate and will enjoy the drop in grade. The one to beat. WILDSPITZE (5) comes out of the same race and was beaten a mile well supported. He was vet cleared and had been in the money prior at Gold Coast. Will get every chance to turn things around. MISTER MIGHTY (1) was in the firing line on the turn over 1400m at Gatton, beaten 1.5L. He keeps improving, and we can anticipate another bold run. ZHONGXIN KOALA (6) was much better beaten 2.3L at Ipswich over 1350m. Has a low gate and key gear switch on a 6-day return. He can fill a slot.
